The Quest For The Holy Foreskin

History Documentary hosted by David Farley, published by National Geographic in 2013 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

The Quest For The Holy Foreskin
For centuries, the relic of the Holy Foreskin was considered by believers to be the only piece of Jesus' flesh to remain on earth after he ascended to heaven, and thus was among the most sacred relics in Christendom. Then, on New Year's Day 1983, in a tiny village in the Italian countryside, Father Don Dario announced to his expectant flock that their beloved relic had been stolen. In The Quest for the Holy Foreskin we will follow writer David Farley on his mission to find out what happened to the Holy Foreskin. He has been offered a certified Holy Foreskin by an Italian relic dealer. Could this be the relic that went missing from Calcata? With the relic in his possession, Farley will try to find out if it could be the real Foreskin of Jesus Christ. He will visit DNA laboratories in Germany and infiltrate the Vatican in his search for answers. Farley will also discover the legend of the Holy Foreskin and the crucial role it played in European history. Ultimately he will go to Calcata to confront priest Don Dario and reveal the truth once and for all.

